Pip 🥥 🌙 2023-11-24 7:28 AM
DISCLAIMER: PIP DOES NOT ENCOURAGE OR CONDONE TEEN MARRIAGE, CHILDREN IN LEADERSHIP ROLES IN CHURCHES, OR REDUCING THE AIR FORCE TO 'FALLING OUT OF PLANES'. In my dream the whole family was invited to visit for the day for free this big old stately home with gardens that was open to the public. It was connected to this massive very old private school and I had an interview there in the morning of our visit. They didn’t give any details about the interview (except for something about marriage, but that ends up being nearly completely irrelevant) and for some reason we didn’t question it. But then the time of our visit was moved and we assumed the interview had been cancelled. We arrived, had a great day out, twas fun. As we were about to leave, it occurred to me that the interview might not have been cancelled, just merely moved and that we were very late. So I quickly hurried in and found the man who wanted to interview me, he was mildly annoyed at my lateness. Apparently they needed a new priest/vicar for the school. I was a bit shocked at being chosen as I was not Church of England, was only 16 (this happened next summer for some reason), completely unknown to the school, had no experience in this sort of stuff and was a girl/woman (I don’t believe women should hold major leadership roles in the church, but lets not debate it.) I knew he had considered all these factors, so I did my best not to question it. Due to my previously stated views, I asked if could a boy be found who I could marry and he could do all the major bits and I would assist him. The man immediately replied by telling me that this boy called Connor had just joined the air force for work experience and couldn’t very well preach if he was busy falling out of a plane. (For some reason this was meant to be the boy I had a HUGE crush on for a while, but Connor isn’t his real name.) And that was roughly where the dream ended. A lot more happened, but these are just the main points. (edited)
